WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.235 --> 00:00:02.169
[Franklin]
<i>Previously on</i> Will Trent...

2
00:00:03.437 --> 00:00:05.339
Got to the point where I'd look
in the mirror and didn't know

3
00:00:05.472 --> 00:00:07.074
who I was looking at.

4
00:00:07.207 --> 00:00:09.544
Then Gina. she found a meeting
that I could go to.
Talking helps.

5
00:00:09.677 --> 00:00:13.615
The best part of this drink is
it comes with a fun umbrella.

6
00:00:14.949 --> 00:00:16.651
-Antonio!
-I'll check the back.

7
00:00:16.784 --> 00:00:17.719
[Will] Antonio!

8
00:00:17.852 --> 00:00:18.953
<i>He's gone.</i>

9
00:00:19.086 --> 00:00:20.655
James Ulster's been dead
for nearly two months.

10
00:00:20.788 --> 00:00:21.890
That's what you think.

11
00:00:22.022 --> 00:00:24.358
I got a letter.
That's how he talked to me.

12
00:00:24.491 --> 00:00:26.226
That's how
he talked to all of us.

13
00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:28.328
[James] <i>If I had nothing to do</i>
<i>with sending those letters...</i>

14
00:00:28.462 --> 00:00:31.699
Then there's someone else
who knows about Antonio.
my mother. everything.

15
00:00:31.833 --> 00:00:33.568
-Where's my uncle?
-Guess you'll never know.

16
00:00:34.167 --> 00:00:35.168
Where is he?

17
00:00:35.302 --> 00:00:36.236
[Faith] <i>What happened?</i>

18
00:00:36.370 --> 00:00:38.338
Spiders. Poison.

19
00:00:38.472 --> 00:00:42.376
Hey. hey. Will. stay with me.
Help is on the way.
Will. stay with me.

20
00:00:45.212 --> 00:00:47.247
[rhythmic beeping echoes]

21
00:00:54.689 --> 00:00:56.056
[muffled PA announcement]

22
00:00:58.893 --> 00:01:00.093
Ang.

23
00:01:01.295 --> 00:01:03.297
Hey. you're awake.

24
00:01:04.364 --> 00:01:05.399
How do you feel?

25
00:01:05.533 --> 00:01:08.002
[groans] Weird.

26
00:01:08.703 --> 00:01:09.938
[groans] Dizzy.

27
00:01:10.070 --> 00:01:12.674
Yeah. they gave you antivenom
for the spider bites

28
00:01:12.807 --> 00:01:16.945
and a sedative
because you were in a state.

29
00:01:18.646 --> 00:01:19.681
Oh.

30
00:01:21.516 --> 00:01:24.986
Yeah. you were trying to pull
out your IV. go after Antonio.

31
00:01:27.487 --> 00:01:29.724
-What do you know?
-What we know is that

32
00:01:30.190 --> 00:01:32.627
Adelaide was spotted in Brazil.

33
00:01:33.528 --> 00:01:35.029
We don't know if he's with her.

34
00:01:35.763 --> 00:01:38.231
-The FBI has. like.
a whole team on it...
-[sighs]

35
00:01:38.365 --> 00:01:40.802
...and they're
doing their FBI thing.

36
00:01:40.935 --> 00:01:44.171
I need to... I gotta...
I gotta go do something
to help. [groans]

37
00:01:44.304 --> 00:01:45.640
-Hey.
-Oh. can you get me
out of here?

38
00:01:45.773 --> 00:01:48.009
-Will. you just woke up
five seconds ago.
-[exhales]

39
00:01:48.141 --> 00:01:51.278
Can you please take some time
to recover from almost dying

40
00:01:51.411 --> 00:01:53.146
before you beat
yourself up again?

41
00:01:55.215 --> 00:01:58.052
-[sighs] He's my family. Ang.
-[softly] I know.

42
00:01:58.185 --> 00:02:01.956
I know. And they will tell me
as soon as they learn anything.

43
00:02:02.557 --> 00:02:03.758
They're gonna find him.

44
00:02:08.663 --> 00:02:09.731
Did you sleep here?

45
00:02:10.297 --> 00:02:11.298
Of course.

46
00:02:12.800 --> 00:02:14.167
You're my family.

47
00:02:19.874 --> 00:02:21.743
Let me get somebody
to handle those straps.

48
00:02:21.876 --> 00:02:23.276
You must be starving.

49
00:02:23.745 --> 00:02:26.380
I'll have Seth make someone
bring you the good meat loaf.

50
00:02:27.414 --> 00:02:28.916
Is there such a thing?

51
00:02:29.050 --> 00:02:31.552
Well. trust me. you don't
want the bad one. [chuckles]

52
00:02:31.686 --> 00:02:32.954
[♪ upbeat music playing]

53
00:02:34.254 --> 00:02:35.890
[Franklin] <i>So you're</i>
<i>the one who found him?</i>

54
00:02:36.024 --> 00:02:40.394
Yeah. this morning I noticed
the door was wide open.
found him inside.

55
00:02:40.528 --> 00:02:42.697
-Now I gotta do a deep-clean.
-[siren wails]

56
00:02:42.830 --> 00:02:44.464
Yeah. that sounds
like a hassle.

57
00:02:45.099 --> 00:02:46.299
You got a name?

58
00:02:46.433 --> 00:02:47.902
No. he paid cash.

59
00:02:48.036 --> 00:02:49.302
Did you get his ID?

60
00:02:49.837 --> 00:02:52.140
This look like the kind
of place that checks IDs?

61
00:02:53.641 --> 00:02:55.175
Can't find
the guy's wallet anywhere.

62
00:02:55.308 --> 00:02:56.644
Door's wide open.

63
00:02:56.778 --> 00:02:58.646
Anyone could have lifted it
after the fact.

64
00:02:59.847 --> 00:03:03.250
And he definitely had money.
The guy's sweater's worth more
than my mortgage.

65
00:03:05.385 --> 00:03:08.455
Okay. so headphones. keyboard.

66
00:03:10.091 --> 00:03:12.560
This notebook's
full of music stuff.

67
00:03:13.326 --> 00:03:14.696
[Franklin] Music stuff?

68
00:03:14.829 --> 00:03:16.831
[Michael]
Yeah. Franklin. music stuff.

69
00:03:16.964 --> 00:03:20.333
Sheet music.
musical notations. composing.

70
00:03:21.069 --> 00:03:23.171
Why would a rich guy
work from this dump?

71
00:03:23.303 --> 00:03:26.339
Drugs? We got some white powder
here. Looks like cocaine.

72
00:03:26.473 --> 00:03:29.376
-Yeah.
-And what do we have here?
Adderall.

73
00:03:29.944 --> 00:03:31.079
Is there a name on the bottle?

74
00:03:31.211 --> 00:03:32.714
Uh. label's torn.
Hard to make it out.

75
00:03:32.847 --> 00:03:34.749
Hey. let's get this.
uh. logged and bagged.

76
00:03:34.882 --> 00:03:38.285
So. doing a little coke.
tickling the ivories.

77
00:03:38.418 --> 00:03:40.688
Sounds like a fun night
till he got shot.

78
00:03:41.556 --> 00:03:42.924
[♪ playing "Chopsticks"]

79
00:03:49.496 --> 00:03:50.565
Did Cooper teach you that?

80
00:03:50.698 --> 00:03:53.366
[scoffs] Cooper has
nowhere near my skills.

81
00:03:54.836 --> 00:03:56.303
Hey.

82
00:03:56.436 --> 00:03:58.940
this keyboard case
says "property of
Atlanta City Orchestra."

83
00:03:59.073 --> 00:04:00.041
[♪ dramatic music plays]

84
00:04:00.174 --> 00:04:01.209
Oh. no.

85
00:04:01.876 --> 00:04:03.111
I know who this is.

86
00:04:03.578 --> 00:04:05.213
Who?

87
00:04:05.345 --> 00:04:07.882
It's Ronaldo Benetti.
the conductor
of the Atlanta City Orchestra.

88
00:04:08.015 --> 00:04:09.117
Why "Oh. no"?

89
00:04:10.918 --> 00:04:13.955
'Cause a man is dead. and
every life lost is a tragedy.

90
00:04:14.088 --> 00:04:15.322
Yeah.

91
00:04:15.455 --> 00:04:16.624
But really. why "Oh. no"?

92
00:04:17.191 --> 00:04:18.425
I'm a patron of the arts.

93
00:04:19.392 --> 00:04:21.763
-Since when?
-Oh. you know.

94
00:04:22.897 --> 00:04:24.699
I go to the symphony.

95
00:04:24.832 --> 00:04:27.400
Why are you acting so weird
right now? Since when do you
go to the symphony?

96
00:04:27.535 --> 00:04:30.972
During my personal
private life.
which you know nothing about.

97
00:04:32.707 --> 00:04:34.776
Do we have to go
to Symphony Hall now?

98
00:04:35.576 --> 00:04:37.779
Seems like we do. Yeah.

99
00:04:37.912 --> 00:04:39.479
[♪ "Make a Change" playing]

100
00:04:39.614 --> 00:04:44.417
We've got two eggs.
half a bell pepper.
and some wilted spinach.

101
00:04:46.687 --> 00:04:48.355
I could make you an omelet.

102
00:04:49.957 --> 00:04:51.391
I'm not hungry.

103
00:04:52.160 --> 00:04:53.326
I just had meat loaf.

104
00:04:53.460 --> 00:04:55.263
Okay. How about some tea?

105
00:04:56.329 --> 00:04:57.965
Yeah. sure.

106
00:05:00.234 --> 00:05:04.371
♪ <i>How long. baby. how long...</i> ♪

107
00:05:07.374 --> 00:05:10.011
♪ <i>Will this madness</i>
<i>be here to stay?</i> ♪

108
00:05:14.481 --> 00:05:15.516
[grunts]

109
00:05:16.449 --> 00:05:18.485
[straining. grunting]

110
00:05:18.619 --> 00:05:20.054
I hate this floor.

111
00:05:22.056 --> 00:05:23.423
Yeah. me too.

112
00:05:23.925 --> 00:05:25.993
Okay. let's get rid
of the floor.

113
00:05:27.295 --> 00:05:28.328
[Nico chuckles]

114
00:05:28.830 --> 00:05:29.997
[Will grunts]

115
00:05:30.631 --> 00:05:33.433
Is there a plan
or are we just deconstructing?

116
00:05:33.568 --> 00:05:34.836
[Will panting]

117
00:05:34.969 --> 00:05:37.370
You know.
that-that's a good question.

118
00:05:37.505 --> 00:05:41.709
Um. how about you. uh.
go to the hardware store. huh?

119
00:05:41.843 --> 00:05:45.378
And grab
some-some linoleum samples?

120
00:05:45.513 --> 00:05:47.315
Okay.

121
00:05:47.447 --> 00:05:48.716
Come on. Betty.

122
00:05:49.416 --> 00:05:50.618
Let's go shopping.

123
00:05:53.087 --> 00:05:54.288
[♪ somber music plays]

124
00:05:55.857 --> 00:05:57.158
[breathes heavily]

125
00:06:03.564 --> 00:06:05.299
[grunting. groaning]

126
00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:08.202
[panting. whimpering]

127
00:06:11.539 --> 00:06:13.207
There. there.

128
00:06:15.843 --> 00:06:17.311
I'm so over you.

129
00:06:17.444 --> 00:06:18.746
-[James chuckles]
-[Will sighs]

130
00:06:18.880 --> 00:06:21.315
As horrible as this floor is.

131
00:06:21.448 --> 00:06:23.584
I think our efforts would
be better spent elsewhere.

132
00:06:24.185 --> 00:06:29.690
You really think it's wise
to leave the search
for Adelaide to the FBI?

133
00:06:29.824 --> 00:06:33.594
[scoffs] There is no "our."

134
00:06:34.195 --> 00:06:35.696
All right? It's all your fault.

135
00:06:37.064 --> 00:06:40.101
[sighs] I can't believe
you were allowed to procreate.

136
00:06:40.234 --> 00:06:41.602
Oh. look on the bright side.

137
00:06:41.736 --> 00:06:43.436
Who's better qualified than you

138
00:06:43.571 --> 00:06:47.141
to track down a deranged James
Ulster obsessive? [cackles]

139
00:06:47.708 --> 00:06:49.877
Come on. Will.
Where should we start?

140
00:06:51.345 --> 00:06:52.412
Her mother.

141
00:06:52.947 --> 00:06:54.582
[♪ tense music plays]

142
00:06:57.251 --> 00:06:58.319
I'm doing better.

143
00:06:59.220 --> 00:07:00.588
Fewer flashbacks.

144
00:07:02.089 --> 00:07:03.291
But it's hard.

145
00:07:04.158 --> 00:07:05.559
I still don't feel like myself.

146
00:07:06.761 --> 00:07:08.296
I'm used to being in control.

147
00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:12.833
I'm the one who protects
the people I love.

148
00:07:17.705 --> 00:07:20.274
You know. lately I've been
thinking about buildings.

149
00:07:21.409 --> 00:07:24.512
You know how the ones built
with some give... [inhales]

150
00:07:25.313 --> 00:07:27.348
...they're the ones
that survive earthquakes.

151
00:07:28.049 --> 00:07:30.418
But the ones that are rigid...

152
00:07:32.653 --> 00:07:34.422
they're the ones
that just crumble.

153
00:07:35.222 --> 00:07:37.591
I have to believe that. um.

154
00:07:37.725 --> 00:07:41.896
finding a way to move with
the ground shifting under me...

155
00:07:44.899 --> 00:07:46.567
it's the only way to survive.

156
00:07:50.470 --> 00:07:51.539
Oh. hey.

157
00:07:51.672 --> 00:07:54.508
That was really beautiful.
what you said.

158
00:07:55.609 --> 00:07:56.877
Oh. thank you. Casey.

159
00:07:57.812 --> 00:07:58.846
Mmm.

160
00:07:59.513 --> 00:08:02.116
-Have you seen
your ex's truck this week?
-Couple of times.

161
00:08:02.249 --> 00:08:03.851
Still parked down
at the end of the block?

162
00:08:03.985 --> 00:08:05.753
Hundred yards to the inch.

163
00:08:05.886 --> 00:08:06.921
[Amanda sighs]

164
00:08:08.656 --> 00:08:10.324
Well. if he comes any closer.
you call me.

165
00:08:10.458 --> 00:08:12.927
I'll get his ass on violating
that restraining order.

166
00:08:13.060 --> 00:08:16.397
Wow. You weren't kidding when
you said you were protective.

167
00:08:16.530 --> 00:08:17.631
[chuckles]

168
00:08:18.632 --> 00:08:19.767
I like it.

169
00:08:20.434 --> 00:08:22.103
I like seeing you alive.

170
00:08:22.970 --> 00:08:28.042
Uh. do you want to have
dinner tonight at my place?

171
00:08:31.212 --> 00:08:32.380
I'll bring the wine.

172
00:08:32.513 --> 00:08:34.749
[♪ orchestral music playing]

173
00:08:40.688 --> 00:08:43.758
Hey. guys.
The GBI just got tagged in.

174
00:08:43.891 --> 00:08:46.127
Apparently Ronaldo Benetti
is kind of a big deal.

175
00:08:46.260 --> 00:08:48.629
-Oh. yeah.
Franklin's a big fan.
-Oh.

176
00:08:48.763 --> 00:08:50.498
There's something weird
going on. and he won't tell me.

177
00:08:50.631 --> 00:08:52.500
But he did do a whitening
strip on the way over.

178
00:08:52.633 --> 00:08:54.568
What happened
to partner code. man?

179
00:08:54.702 --> 00:08:55.836
You got anything new for us?

180
00:08:55.970 --> 00:08:57.872
Yeah. I talked to Pete
on the way out.

181
00:08:58.005 --> 00:09:00.274
Cause of death is a gunshot.
but get this.

182
00:09:00.408 --> 00:09:02.009
victim had postmortem bruising.

183
00:09:02.511 --> 00:09:04.879
So whoever did this shot him
and then beat him up?

184
00:09:05.012 --> 00:09:06.180
They really hated this guy.

185
00:09:07.848 --> 00:09:10.017
[♪ orchestral music continues]

186
00:09:14.688 --> 00:09:17.324
-We should interview
all these people.
-Yep.

187
00:09:17.458 --> 00:09:18.926
I'll take the trumpet player.

188
00:09:21.328 --> 00:09:23.431
Sorry. is there no one else
who can do this interview?

189
00:09:23.564 --> 00:09:25.666
It's stressful enough
that Ronaldo
was apparently murdered.

190
00:09:25.800 --> 00:09:26.734
and now you show up.

191
00:09:26.867 --> 00:09:28.035
Oh. it's just business. Leon.

192
00:09:28.169 --> 00:09:30.539
-Mmm.
-Do you take
prescription medication?

193
00:09:30.671 --> 00:09:32.373
You know that I do.
Why is that relevant?

194
00:09:32.507 --> 00:09:35.009
Oh. 'cause we found a bottle
of Adderall at the crime scene.

195
00:09:35.544 --> 00:09:38.946
and the letters on the label
seem to match your name.

196
00:09:40.381 --> 00:09:44.051
Okay. look. Ronaldo.
he was under a ton of pressure.

197
00:09:44.185 --> 00:09:45.586
He was having trouble
getting work done.

198
00:09:45.719 --> 00:09:47.955
so he asked if I could share
some of my meds with him.

199
00:09:48.089 --> 00:09:49.590
So I gave him a few pills.

200
00:09:49.723 --> 00:09:51.058
What kind of pressure?

201
00:09:51.192 --> 00:09:53.594
We have a big performance
coming up.

202
00:09:53.727 --> 00:09:56.363
We're doing Ronaldo's
original composition.

203
00:09:56.997 --> 00:09:58.466
So. he was a composer too?

204
00:09:58.599 --> 00:10:01.068
Uh. he talked about it a lot.

205
00:10:01.202 --> 00:10:03.170
This was the first one
he actually finished.

206
00:10:03.304 --> 00:10:05.739
But it took forever
for Ronaldo to show it to us.

207
00:10:05.873 --> 00:10:08.676
He was acting
more and more erratic.

208
00:10:08.809 --> 00:10:11.745
[stutters]
Everyone was starting to
freak out. especially Claudia.

209
00:10:11.879 --> 00:10:14.982
-Who's Claudia?
-The executive director
of the symphony.

210
00:10:15.116 --> 00:10:17.785
Claudia was afraid that
we would have nothing to play.

211
00:10:17.918 --> 00:10:19.653
that we'd have to
call the whole thing off.

212
00:10:19.787 --> 00:10:23.090
But then. finally...
[sighs] ...after disappearing
for. like. 24 hours.

213
00:10:23.224 --> 00:10:26.193
Ronaldo showed up yesterday.
said he was finished.

214
00:10:27.261 --> 00:10:29.396
And it's annoyingly brilliant.

215
00:10:29.531 --> 00:10:31.031
How long is this gonna take?

216
00:10:31.165 --> 00:10:34.001
Lila. honey. um. let's let
the detectives do their job.

217
00:10:34.135 --> 00:10:36.804
Tom. you're always
trying to manage me. Just...

218
00:10:36.937 --> 00:10:37.972
I-I need a cigarette.

219
00:10:38.472 --> 00:10:39.673
-That's fine.
-Thank you.

220
00:10:39.807 --> 00:10:42.109
Pippa. are we still performing
or what?

221
00:10:42.243 --> 00:10:44.145
I don't know. [stutters]

222
00:10:44.278 --> 00:10:46.247
-Is your solo ready?
-Yes. of course it is.

223
00:10:46.380 --> 00:10:47.616
Brass. on the other hand. mess.

224
00:10:47.748 --> 00:10:49.450
She hums Ronaldo's
soaring melody

225
00:10:49.584 --> 00:10:53.087
-as she dozes
beside me at night.
-But who's going to conduct it?

226
00:10:55.624 --> 00:10:58.225
I'm very sorry.
Uh. we're both very upset.

227
00:10:58.359 --> 00:10:59.860
-[Lila] Are you coming?
-Yeah.

228
00:11:03.330 --> 00:11:05.065
Where were you
last night. Leon?

229
00:11:06.167 --> 00:11:07.801
You have to answer my question.
You're a suspect.

230
00:11:07.935 --> 00:11:09.203
I'm a suspect?

231
00:11:09.336 --> 00:11:11.506
You're not not a suspect.
You gave a dead man drugs.

232
00:11:11.640 --> 00:11:13.407
-Adderall.
-It's a controlled substance.

233
00:11:13.542 --> 00:11:15.610
Seriously.
Franklin. come on. you know me.

234
00:11:15.743 --> 00:11:17.678
Oh. you know. I thought I did.

235
00:11:17.811 --> 00:11:20.381
-Be honest.
Are you punishing me?
-Just give me an alibi.

236
00:11:20.515 --> 00:11:22.483
I was at my boyfriend's
all night.

237
00:11:23.585 --> 00:11:25.853
-Boyfriend?
-There's a camera in the lobby

238
00:11:25.986 --> 00:11:27.221
that you can check.

239
00:11:29.356 --> 00:11:31.325
Now just ask me what
you really want to know.

240
00:11:31.458 --> 00:11:34.228
Well... [inhales]
...I mean. I am curious.

241
00:11:34.895 --> 00:11:36.397
Four months of happy dating.

242
00:11:36.964 --> 00:11:39.967
I had a drawer at your place.
you had a toothbrush at mine.

243
00:11:40.535 --> 00:11:41.670
Why did you ghost me?

244
00:11:41.802 --> 00:11:43.103
[♪ dramatic music plays]

245
00:11:46.307 --> 00:11:47.542
"Not funny."

246
00:11:48.042 --> 00:11:49.910
-He said that?
-I know I made him
laugh before.

247
00:11:50.044 --> 00:11:52.413
I just can't think of any
specific moment right now.

248
00:11:52.547 --> 00:11:54.415
-but I know I did.
-[person] Pippa!

249
00:11:55.216 --> 00:11:56.417
Pippa!

250
00:11:57.484 --> 00:12:00.387
-Where is Pippa?
-Claudia. hi.

251
00:12:00.522 --> 00:12:01.889
Did you hear? How are you?

252
00:12:02.022 --> 00:12:04.825
Yes. it's horrible. I have
grief counselors on their way.

253
00:12:05.527 --> 00:12:09.363
Anyone who needs to avail
themselves can. but please
don't leave the building.

254
00:12:10.130 --> 00:12:11.465
We have to rehearse.

255
00:12:12.299 --> 00:12:13.901
We're not canceling the show?

256
00:12:14.502 --> 00:12:17.572
-[softly] Absolutely not.
-I'm sorry. Why not?

257
00:12:17.706 --> 00:12:19.574
It's not what
Ronaldo would want.

258
00:12:20.207 --> 00:12:22.443
We owe it to him to let
his magnum opus be heard.

259
00:12:24.679 --> 00:12:26.715
Pippa. we need a conductor.

260
00:12:26.847 --> 00:12:28.115
[♪ playful music plays]

261
00:12:28.683 --> 00:12:29.783
Can you do it?

262
00:12:30.619 --> 00:12:31.653
Yes.

263
00:12:33.521 --> 00:12:35.789
Good. Go tell everyone.

264
00:12:38.727 --> 00:12:40.294
Hi. Sorry about that.

265
00:12:40.427 --> 00:12:43.430
Claudia Sobinsky. executive
director. How can I help?

266
00:12:43.565 --> 00:12:45.600
Well. we need to
see Ronaldo's office.

267
00:12:47.134 --> 00:12:48.802
-Right this way.
-Thank you.

268
00:12:48.936 --> 00:12:51.305
Sounds like Ronaldo
was acting erratic recently.

269
00:12:51.438 --> 00:12:54.942
I've known Ronaldo
for 25 years. since our
music school days.

270
00:12:55.577 --> 00:12:56.944
I'd never seen him like this.

271
00:12:57.077 --> 00:12:58.479
It was this composition.

272
00:12:59.079 --> 00:13:01.849
I told him he was already
a great conductor.

273
00:13:01.982 --> 00:13:05.620
He didn't need
to compose. but... [inhales]
...he wouldn't listen.

274
00:13:05.754 --> 00:13:08.022
He just put so much pressure
on himself.

275
00:13:08.155 --> 00:13:10.291
How was it that it came down
to the last second like this?

276
00:13:10.424 --> 00:13:13.260
He insisted I schedule
his debut as the highlight
of our season.

277
00:13:13.394 --> 00:13:16.363
even hinged his entire
contract renegotiation on it.

278
00:13:16.497 --> 00:13:18.265
And then. once
everything was signed.

279
00:13:18.399 --> 00:13:21.235
it turned out
he hadn't even written it yet.

280
00:13:21.368 --> 00:13:23.370
That's why he didn't
want Pippa to see it.

281
00:13:23.505 --> 00:13:25.507
I've been close
to a heart attack waiting.

282
00:13:25.640 --> 00:13:29.511
But yesterday.
Ronaldo showed up with
a completed chamber piece.

283
00:13:29.644 --> 00:13:32.647
and it was everything
he'd promised.

284
00:13:33.748 --> 00:13:34.882
It was stunning.

285
00:13:35.449 --> 00:13:36.950
Ronaldo have issues
with anyone here?

286
00:13:38.152 --> 00:13:40.522
He was a giant pain
in the ass. but. uh.

287
00:13:41.690 --> 00:13:42.823
he was our maestro.

288
00:13:44.158 --> 00:13:45.959
Everyone worshipped him.

289
00:13:47.361 --> 00:13:50.565
Yeah. I can relate.
I play a little myself.

290
00:13:51.332 --> 00:13:53.601
Really. man? Every time? Ugh.

291
00:13:53.735 --> 00:13:56.070
You know what. don't do that.
Please don't do that.

292
00:13:56.203 --> 00:13:57.237
[rattling]

293
00:13:59.239 --> 00:14:00.374
That's weird.

294
00:14:02.376 --> 00:14:03.410
[Claudia gasps]

295
00:14:04.445 --> 00:14:05.680
[♪ eerie music plays]

296
00:14:07.582 --> 00:14:09.684
I guess someone here
didn't worship Ronaldo.

297
00:14:09.818 --> 00:14:10.884
At all.

298
00:14:12.787 --> 00:14:15.724
I already told the FBI.

299
00:14:15.856 --> 00:14:17.858
I don't know where Adelaide is.

300
00:14:17.991 --> 00:14:23.665
Oh. no. of course. but.
um... [sighs] ...if you could
think of anything else.

301
00:14:23.798 --> 00:14:26.367
anything at all
that might help us find her.

302
00:14:26.500 --> 00:14:27.736
we'd appreciate it.

303
00:14:27.868 --> 00:14:34.441
Uh. there was always
something off with that girl.

304
00:14:35.142 --> 00:14:37.378
Chip off the old block. Maybe
I was wrong to reject her.

305
00:14:37.512 --> 00:14:40.749
Speaking of. all those
letters Adelaide sent me.

306
00:14:41.415 --> 00:14:44.485
-I sent them back unopened.
-[Ms. Trevens continues.
indistinct]

307
00:14:44.619 --> 00:14:47.187
Maybe they're
around here somewhere.

308
00:14:48.021 --> 00:14:53.093
I tried to set
Adelaide on the right path.

309
00:14:54.194 --> 00:14:59.299
But no matter
how long I kept her

310
00:14:59.433 --> 00:15:00.869
in the wardrobe.

311
00:15:01.569 --> 00:15:02.871
nothing happened.

312
00:15:03.003 --> 00:15:04.037
The wardrobe?

313
00:15:05.939 --> 00:15:10.545
[sighs] It's our little
nickname for time-out.

314
00:15:11.145 --> 00:15:14.481
I had to send her there
when she misbehaved.

315
00:15:14.616 --> 00:15:16.551
Uh-oh. bad mommy.

316
00:15:16.684 --> 00:15:18.853
[Ms. Trevens]
...discipline your children...

317
00:15:19.019 --> 00:15:20.655
I don't know why
I had sex with this woman.

318
00:15:20.789 --> 00:15:21.823
[sighs]

319
00:15:23.357 --> 00:15:24.726
[clears throat] Um...

320
00:15:26.326 --> 00:15:29.463
Ms. Trevens. could
I... Could I trouble you
for a glass of water?

321
00:15:29.597 --> 00:15:31.198
[imitating cough]

322
00:15:31.331 --> 00:15:32.466
[Will] Thank you.

323
00:15:35.737 --> 00:15:37.337
[Ms. Trevens huffs]

324
00:15:39.000 --> 00:15:45.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

325
00:15:58.225 --> 00:16:00.327
Oh.

326
00:16:01.596 --> 00:16:03.565
Now. this is twisted.

327
00:16:04.198 --> 00:16:05.432
Even for me.

328
00:16:06.901 --> 00:16:08.435
She was just a kid.

329
00:16:09.970 --> 00:16:11.972
I should arrest
this lady for child abuse.

330
00:16:12.105 --> 00:16:15.309
No. keep your eye
on the ball. You haven't
looked in there yet.

331
00:16:21.215 --> 00:16:23.317
[chuckles] You're welcome.

332
00:16:23.450 --> 00:16:24.485
Oh. shut up.

333
00:16:24.619 --> 00:16:26.521
You're me. Stop taking credit.

334
00:16:31.124 --> 00:16:35.429
This is you entering Ronaldo's
office three days ago.

335
00:16:36.230 --> 00:16:38.666
We know you
destroyed his piano.

336
00:16:38.800 --> 00:16:41.001
We saw the damage.
Now that is real hatred.

337
00:16:41.134 --> 00:16:44.639
You've been assistant conductor
for what. six years now?

338
00:16:45.272 --> 00:16:47.675
It's a long time
to play second fiddle.

339
00:16:47.809 --> 00:16:50.778
It's not easy to stand on
the sidelines. watch somebody
else live your dreams.

340
00:16:50.912 --> 00:16:52.614
I mean. it makes sense
to resent him.

341
00:16:52.747 --> 00:16:55.850
Sometimes that's easier
than admitting maybe you
don't have what it takes.

342
00:16:55.984 --> 00:16:57.484
I do have what it takes.

343
00:16:58.318 --> 00:17:00.722
The passion. the focus.
the commitment.

344
00:17:00.855 --> 00:17:03.190
That bastard tried to break me.
but I'm still here.

345
00:17:03.323 --> 00:17:08.328
Yeah. Yeah. you are.
front and center on
the symphony's biggest night.

346
00:17:08.462 --> 00:17:10.330
What? No.

347
00:17:10.464 --> 00:17:11.833
It's finally
working out for you.

348
00:17:13.001 --> 00:17:16.103
Okay. fine. I destroyed the
piano. but I didn't kill him.

349
00:17:16.236 --> 00:17:18.372
Yeah. well. you certainly
killed that piano.

350
00:17:19.507 --> 00:17:22.744
What exactly did Ronaldo
do to make you so angry?

351
00:17:22.877 --> 00:17:27.281
He belittled my conducting.
the way I dressed.
my music knowledge.

352
00:17:27.882 --> 00:17:30.518
For years. he told me I'd
never make it as a conductor

353
00:17:30.652 --> 00:17:32.419
and refused to give me
a recommendation.

354
00:17:34.556 --> 00:17:36.925
He knew about the piano.
by the way.

355
00:17:37.491 --> 00:17:40.394
When he saw what I'd done.
he was impressed.

356
00:17:40.528 --> 00:17:42.764
He said it was about time
I showed some teeth.

357
00:17:44.866 --> 00:17:46.868
I swear I didn't kill him.

358
00:17:47.001 --> 00:17:49.904
I-I didn't want to get the job
this way. I wanted to earn it.

359
00:17:51.706 --> 00:17:54.909
Is there anything
you can tell us about
Ronaldo's disappearance

360
00:17:55.043 --> 00:17:56.811
the day before
he delivered the composition?

361
00:17:56.945 --> 00:17:58.580
Um...

362
00:17:58.713 --> 00:18:01.281
All-All I know is
when I asked how he managed
to finish the piece.

363
00:18:01.415 --> 00:18:03.785
he told me he'd found his muse.

364
00:18:05.218 --> 00:18:06.554
Any idea who
he was referring to?

365
00:18:06.688 --> 00:18:09.958
No. I just figured
that meant he'd gotten laid.

366
00:18:10.090 --> 00:18:12.225
Guy was hornier
than a jackrabbit. Ugh.

367
00:18:12.894 --> 00:18:14.094
[Michael. Franklin] Hmm.

368
00:18:14.227 --> 00:18:16.731
Hey. they found
Ronaldo's car abandoned.

369
00:18:16.864 --> 00:18:18.766
It's being towed to
the impound lot. Let's go.

370
00:18:18.900 --> 00:18:20.200
[♪ suspenseful music plays]

371
00:18:30.078 --> 00:18:31.278
[knocks on door]

372
00:18:35.016 --> 00:18:36.050
Hey.

373
00:18:36.851 --> 00:18:38.886
Yeah. I thought
you might be working.

374
00:18:39.787 --> 00:18:41.756
-Brought Szechuan.
-Oh. where's Seth?

375
00:18:41.889 --> 00:18:45.526
He is drinking a nonalcoholic
beer and watching a documentary
on Dunkirk.

376
00:18:45.660 --> 00:18:49.296
-Hi. baby.
Oh. I missed you. Come here.
-[Betty whines. yelps]

377
00:18:50.230 --> 00:18:53.801
Oh. help me take this food
to the dining table.
will you? Yeah?

378
00:18:54.468 --> 00:18:55.637
So what do you got?

379
00:18:55.770 --> 00:18:58.372
Adelaide's letters
to Ulster in prison.

380
00:18:58.506 --> 00:18:59.540
Oh.

381
00:19:00.508 --> 00:19:02.944
You want to read 'em
to me over egg rolls?

382
00:19:03.077 --> 00:19:04.277
Perfect night.

383
00:19:05.613 --> 00:19:07.081
What's up with your kitchen?

384
00:19:07.815 --> 00:19:10.818
Oh. i-it's nothing.
It... Don't worry about it.

385
00:19:13.253 --> 00:19:17.324
"She is stupid
and never listens to me.
I hate her. I hate her.

386
00:19:17.457 --> 00:19:21.996
I wish you'd never met her.
Please show me how to kill her.

387
00:19:22.130 --> 00:19:24.699
I'll do anything.
Your daughter. Adelaide."

388
00:19:24.832 --> 00:19:27.035
You say you had
a flirtation with this woman?

389
00:19:27.167 --> 00:19:29.236
We were in the jungle.

390
00:19:29.369 --> 00:19:32.172
It was very hot and. um.
my guard was down.

391
00:19:32.305 --> 00:19:34.408
[stutters] Look. I've
been very vulnerable lately.

392
00:19:38.079 --> 00:19:39.514
[sighs]

393
00:19:39.647 --> 00:19:41.616
Adelaide never stood a chance.

394
00:19:41.749 --> 00:19:43.017
Abusive mother. no friends.

395
00:19:43.151 --> 00:19:45.887
She could've been us.
She could've.

396
00:19:46.888 --> 00:19:49.657
But we had each other.

397
00:19:51.358 --> 00:19:52.560
[Will chuckles]

398
00:19:54.629 --> 00:19:56.564
-You changed your hair.
-Yeah.

399
00:19:57.965 --> 00:19:59.133
Controlling what I can.

400
00:19:59.600 --> 00:20:00.568
[Will chuckles]

401
00:20:01.069 --> 00:20:02.402
I like it.

402
00:20:02.970 --> 00:20:04.204
[both chuckle]

403
00:20:04.337 --> 00:20:08.308
It makes sense that Adelaide
would start a network.

404
00:20:08.442 --> 00:20:10.511
Other people who fell
through the cracks like her.

405
00:20:10.645 --> 00:20:14.882
That network is the best way
to get to Antonio. Has to be.

406
00:20:16.884 --> 00:20:19.087
I gotta take a run
at Jeb Oswald.

407
00:20:20.822 --> 00:20:23.524
-Any advice?
-You're not gonna scare him.

408
00:20:23.658 --> 00:20:25.827
You're not gonna get through
to him with logic.

409
00:20:26.728 --> 00:20:29.731
The only person he wants
to talk to is James Ulster.

410
00:20:33.067 --> 00:20:34.367
I can work with that.

411
00:20:36.003 --> 00:20:37.304
-I don't understand...
-[Amanda chuckles]

412
00:20:37.437 --> 00:20:39.406
Wait. get your hands
off my dishes.

413
00:20:39.540 --> 00:20:41.509
Gosh. you don't know
how to relax. do you?

414
00:20:41.642 --> 00:20:44.244
Let me take care of you
for once. Go. Go away.

415
00:20:44.812 --> 00:20:47.481
Okay. okay. Bossy.

416
00:20:47.615 --> 00:20:49.083
Hmm. takes one to know one.

417
00:20:49.217 --> 00:20:50.985
[chuckles]
You might be right about that.

418
00:20:51.119 --> 00:20:53.221
[♪ "Once in
a Thousand Years" playing]

419
00:20:53.386 --> 00:20:56.289
I took that when I was 18.

420
00:20:56.423 --> 00:21:00.460
I had nothing better to do
than follow a dirt road.
see where it took me.

421
00:21:00.595 --> 00:21:02.462
[chuckles]
I really thought I was a
photographer with that one.

422
00:21:02.597 --> 00:21:05.332
[giggles] Who you telling?

423
00:21:05.465 --> 00:21:08.503
I took a pottery class once
and could have sworn
I was a professional.

424
00:21:08.636 --> 00:21:09.737
[Amanda giggles]

425
00:21:09.871 --> 00:21:11.939
I always said
I'd go back. But...

426
00:21:13.440 --> 00:21:14.609
then I met Dallas and...

427
00:21:16.343 --> 00:21:18.179
-best-laid plans.
-Hmm.

428
00:21:22.784 --> 00:21:23.818
Look.

429
00:21:25.052 --> 00:21:26.754
With everything
you've been going through...

430
00:21:26.888 --> 00:21:28.823
Okay. stop worrying about me.

431
00:21:29.924 --> 00:21:31.759
Start thinking about
what you want.

432
00:21:40.802 --> 00:21:42.302
[Casey chuckles]

433
00:21:43.237 --> 00:21:44.337
Do you want this?

434
00:21:47.642 --> 00:21:48.676
[Amanda chuckles]

435
00:21:57.450 --> 00:21:59.754
-[Amanda inhales. exhales]
-How about this?

436
00:22:11.866 --> 00:22:14.836
[Casey squeals. chuckles]

437
00:22:16.270 --> 00:22:17.805
[both chuckle]

438
00:22:22.977 --> 00:22:27.849
Now. is this the beer bottle
or the coffee pot?

439
00:22:31.451 --> 00:22:32.820
Coffee pot.

440
00:22:37.725 --> 00:22:39.660
You're incredibly brave. Casey.

441
00:22:40.695 --> 00:22:41.729
[chuckles]

442
00:22:49.637 --> 00:22:50.671
So are you.

443
00:23:04.352 --> 00:23:07.221
Don't bother. Amanda.
He always gets away with it.

444
00:23:07.355 --> 00:23:09.090
[♪ tense music plays]

445
00:23:12.560 --> 00:23:14.695
Better have a damn good reason
for hauling me in here.

446
00:23:15.863 --> 00:23:16.864
Why don't you take a seat?

447
00:23:16.998 --> 00:23:18.766
Why don't you tell me
why I'm here?

448
00:23:21.168 --> 00:23:24.105
You threw a rock
through your estranged
wife's window last night.

449
00:23:24.238 --> 00:23:27.541
That's vandalism.
harassment. and a violation
of your restraining order.

450
00:23:27.675 --> 00:23:29.577
I wasn't anywhere near
that bitch's house last night.

451
00:23:29.710 --> 00:23:31.545
I know you've been
parking on Casey's street.

452
00:23:31.679 --> 00:23:32.713
trying to intimidate her.

453
00:23:32.847 --> 00:23:34.048
I can park wherever I want.

454
00:23:34.181 --> 00:23:36.617
I know everything
you put Casey through.

455
00:23:36.751 --> 00:23:39.086
I know every bruise
and every scar.

456
00:23:40.021 --> 00:23:41.222
But that's over now.

457
00:23:42.356 --> 00:23:43.925
You need to leave her alone.

458
00:23:44.058 --> 00:23:45.793
You have no proof. do you?

459
00:23:47.528 --> 00:23:50.398
Looks like you're the one
who's trying to intimidate me.

460
00:23:51.265 --> 00:23:53.401
And I won't be intimidated.

461
00:23:54.434 --> 00:23:57.305
I think this interview is over.
[chuckles]

462
00:24:00.207 --> 00:24:02.643
I met a million guys like you.

463
00:24:02.777 --> 00:24:05.613
Men who think
they're untouchable.

464
00:24:05.746 --> 00:24:09.050
You think you can lay
your hands on anybody you want
and get away with it.

465
00:24:09.183 --> 00:24:12.019
-[chuckles]
-Not this time.

466
00:24:22.196 --> 00:24:25.700
Geez. Faith. this car is
almost as messy as yours is.

467
00:24:25.833 --> 00:24:28.869
-What's with you
creative types?
-Yeah. it's organized chaos.

468
00:24:29.003 --> 00:24:30.237
You know. the thing is...

469
00:24:30.371 --> 00:24:32.373
And look. I don't want
to come across as defensive.

470
00:24:32.506 --> 00:24:34.742
but I am infinitely
funnier than Leon ever was.

471
00:24:34.875 --> 00:24:36.811
Yeah. you're funny.
It's. like. your thing.

472
00:24:36.944 --> 00:24:38.079
What do you mean. my thing?

473
00:24:38.212 --> 00:24:40.247
You know. it's how
you like to be perceived.

474
00:24:41.182 --> 00:24:42.683
You don't think I'm funny?

475
00:24:42.817 --> 00:24:44.051
Faith. am I funny?

476
00:24:44.185 --> 00:24:46.520
-You're not not funny.
-I mean. you're amusing.

477
00:24:46.654 --> 00:24:48.856
-You're fun to have around.
-That is not the same thing.

478
00:24:48.990 --> 00:24:51.258
You don't think I'm funny. You
think Faith is funnier than me?

479
00:24:51.392 --> 00:24:54.295
Leon is lying to you
because he is afraid
of telling you the truth.

480
00:24:54.895 --> 00:24:57.064
Faith. that makes sense.

481
00:24:57.198 --> 00:25:00.134
It's not that I'm not funny.
It is that Leon is a coward.

482
00:25:01.969 --> 00:25:04.772
-Did you find anything?
-Yep. [grunts]

483
00:25:05.506 --> 00:25:07.675
I found this fast-food
receipt from three days ago

484
00:25:07.808 --> 00:25:10.378
during the time that Ronaldo
supposedly disappeared.

485
00:25:10.511 --> 00:25:12.213
He was in Cleveland. Ohio.

486
00:25:12.346 --> 00:25:15.216
And anyone recognize
this lipstick?

487
00:25:17.618 --> 00:25:20.454
We found your cigarettes
in Ronaldo's car.

488
00:25:20.621 --> 00:25:22.390
I think that you two
were having an affair.

489
00:25:22.523 --> 00:25:24.692
Lila. were you his muse?

490
00:25:25.493 --> 00:25:28.262
Sorry. that's what
this is about? [stutters]

491
00:25:28.396 --> 00:25:29.830
I have a solo to rehearse.

492
00:25:29.964 --> 00:25:31.932
What happened?
You break up with him?

493
00:25:32.066 --> 00:25:34.035
He threatened to tell your
husband. so you killed him?

494
00:25:34.168 --> 00:25:37.638
Don't be ridiculous.
Stop. please.
Of course we were intimate.

495
00:25:38.372 --> 00:25:42.143
Profoundly.
passionately. feverishly.

496
00:25:43.244 --> 00:25:46.414
But it wasn't an affair.
because Tom and I
have an arrangement

497
00:25:46.547 --> 00:25:49.417
where we can sleep with
whoever we want as long
as no one falls in love.

498
00:25:49.550 --> 00:25:51.318
and believe me.
I-I never fall in love.

499
00:25:51.452 --> 00:25:53.421
But not with Ronaldo.

500
00:25:53.587 --> 00:25:56.323
We agreed he was
on the no-fly list.

501
00:25:56.457 --> 00:25:58.259
I never agreed
to a no-fly list.

502
00:25:58.392 --> 00:26:01.262
That was just something
that you said. and then
I did not respond to you.

503
00:26:01.395 --> 00:26:04.432
Can... [stutters] What does
it matter? The man is dead.

504
00:26:06.700 --> 00:26:08.402
-Tom...
-Oh. hey. hey. buddy.

505
00:26:08.537 --> 00:26:10.071
Just take it easy. okay?

506
00:26:10.204 --> 00:26:12.239
Don't be hysterical.
It's pedestrian.

507
00:26:12.373 --> 00:26:14.442
Excuse me. what is going on?

508
00:26:14.575 --> 00:26:16.110
Tom. careful of those hands.

509
00:26:16.243 --> 00:26:17.945
-[Lila] Mm-hmm.
-You have to perform tonight.

510
00:26:18.079 --> 00:26:21.315
Do you know anything
about why Ronaldo
might have been in Ohio?

511
00:26:21.449 --> 00:26:24.018
We have a receipt
putting him there
the day before he was killed.

512
00:26:24.985 --> 00:26:26.521
No. I have no idea.

513
00:26:26.687 --> 00:26:29.190
Our relationship
wasn't really based on talking.

514
00:26:29.323 --> 00:26:31.826
-[Tom grunts. groans]
-[feedback whines]

515
00:26:31.959 --> 00:26:33.094
Not really your day. man.

516
00:26:33.227 --> 00:26:35.229
-Ow. I think I broke it.
-No. that's okay.

517
00:26:35.362 --> 00:26:38.399
Yeah. because you don't
play bass with your feet. Here.

518
00:26:38.533 --> 00:26:39.700
Do you want me to come?

519
00:26:39.834 --> 00:26:42.537
[chuckles] I think
you've done enough of that.

520
00:26:43.505 --> 00:26:45.473
Lila. is there anything else
you'd like to share?

521
00:26:45.606 --> 00:26:48.843
I'll just say this.
Whatever he was doing in Ohio.
thank God he went.

522
00:26:48.976 --> 00:26:51.145
-Why do you say that?
-Before he disappeared.

523
00:26:51.278 --> 00:26:52.780
he played me
what he was working on.

524
00:26:52.913 --> 00:26:54.281
It was atrocious.

525
00:26:54.415 --> 00:26:56.250
We were all going
to be publicly humiliated.

526
00:26:56.383 --> 00:26:58.486
Well. what was he doing
for those two days?

527
00:26:58.619 --> 00:27:00.020
I don't know. He never told me.

528
00:27:00.821 --> 00:27:04.091
All I know is I now
have an exquisite violin solo.

529
00:27:04.225 --> 00:27:05.493
It's gonna be...

530
00:27:05.626 --> 00:27:07.361
It's gonna be
career-making. really.

531
00:27:07.495 --> 00:27:10.631
and you should all come
if you can get tickets.

532
00:27:10.764 --> 00:27:13.400
I've given my comps away. but.
uh. look. i-if you'd excuse me.

533
00:27:13.535 --> 00:27:16.170
I-I would really
like to rehearse. So. um...

534
00:27:20.575 --> 00:27:22.209
I don't know about you. Faith.

535
00:27:22.343 --> 00:27:25.146
but I... [exhales]
...think it's time
for Franklin to go on a date.

536
00:27:25.980 --> 00:27:27.781
Oh. absolutely not.

537
00:27:27.915 --> 00:27:29.150
[♪ soul music plays]

538
00:27:31.620 --> 00:27:33.053
This was Ronaldo's composition?

539
00:27:33.187 --> 00:27:34.655
Up until two days ago. yes.

540
00:27:34.788 --> 00:27:37.224
Lila was right. It is very...

541
00:27:38.359 --> 00:27:39.326
amateurish.

542
00:27:39.460 --> 00:27:40.661
I mean. I do not understand

543
00:27:40.794 --> 00:27:42.930
how this became the composition
that Ronaldo turned in.

544
00:27:43.063 --> 00:27:45.866
-Do they resemble
each other at all?
-No. not even close.

545
00:27:46.000 --> 00:27:49.036
That is like it was written by
an entirely different person.

546
00:27:50.137 --> 00:27:52.840
Maybe he stole it and
that's why he ended up dead.

547
00:27:52.973 --> 00:27:55.943
Lord. never underestimate
the audacity of a straight male

548
00:27:56.076 --> 00:27:57.978
with an inflated ego
and a full head of hair.

549
00:27:58.613 --> 00:27:59.680
[chuckles]

550
00:27:59.813 --> 00:28:02.683
Oh. no. no. no.
I know you're not laughing now.

551
00:28:02.816 --> 00:28:04.852
-Oh.
-So now the man thinks
I'm funny. huh?

552
00:28:04.985 --> 00:28:06.020
Mm-hmm.

553
00:28:07.488 --> 00:28:08.523
Tell me the truth.

554
00:28:09.290 --> 00:28:10.324
[Leon sighs]

555
00:28:11.593 --> 00:28:12.661
I don't want kids.

556
00:28:13.662 --> 00:28:15.362
-I know that.
-I like my life.
I like my freedom.

557
00:28:15.496 --> 00:28:17.198
-I do not need kids.
-I specifically said

558
00:28:17.331 --> 00:28:19.099
-I'm okay without having kids.
-But you were lying.

559
00:28:20.000 --> 00:28:21.936
Either to me
or to yourself. okay?

560
00:28:22.069 --> 00:28:24.573
And it just felt
like you thought
that you could wear me down

561
00:28:24.705 --> 00:28:26.807
if you stayed with me
long enough. but I wasn't
gonna change my mind.

562
00:28:26.941 --> 00:28:28.709
-Again.
I specifically said--
-Benjamin.

563
00:28:29.443 --> 00:28:31.812
You know what.
I never should've trusted you
with my first name.

564
00:28:31.946 --> 00:28:34.583
Be honest. Benjamin Franklin.

565
00:28:35.349 --> 00:28:38.687
-Here we go. [sighs]
-You want them.
You do. It's okay.

566
00:28:38.819 --> 00:28:40.387
[chuckles] But God help us.

567
00:28:40.522 --> 00:28:42.856
if there was a child
anywhere near where
we were having brunch.

568
00:28:42.990 --> 00:28:45.426
they were the only ones
getting eye contact.

569
00:28:45.560 --> 00:28:46.894
I did that maybe once.

570
00:28:47.027 --> 00:28:48.996
Mmm. [chuckles]

571
00:28:50.665 --> 00:28:52.366
[sighs] Fine.

572
00:28:53.367 --> 00:28:54.868
I shouldn't have ghosted you.

573
00:28:55.537 --> 00:28:58.540
I actually can't believe
that I did that. It was very...

574
00:29:00.474 --> 00:29:01.676
immature.

575
00:29:05.412 --> 00:29:07.081
Let me make it up to you.

576
00:29:08.415 --> 00:29:11.085
Come to the
performance tonight?
I got you a comp ticket.

577
00:29:11.218 --> 00:29:13.287
-[chuckles] Really?
-That's right.
Best seat in the house.

578
00:29:13.420 --> 00:29:14.455
[Franklin] Wow.

579
00:29:15.256 --> 00:29:16.924
I'd really love
to have you there.

580
00:29:18.025 --> 00:29:20.060
Maybe we can be friends?

581
00:29:22.062 --> 00:29:23.097
Okay.

582
00:29:23.698 --> 00:29:24.733
Okay.

583
00:29:26.100 --> 00:29:28.135
[chains clanking]

584
00:29:36.377 --> 00:29:40.347
[chuckles]
Oh. it's you. Will Trent.

585
00:29:41.282 --> 00:29:43.083
The man who caught
James Ulster.

586
00:29:43.217 --> 00:29:45.786
This is your work. is it not?

587
00:29:47.021 --> 00:29:48.255
-Yep.
-You claim

588
00:29:48.789 --> 00:29:50.424
to be a student
of James Ulster.

589
00:29:50.558 --> 00:29:52.594
I'm more than a student.
I'm an acolyte.

590
00:29:52.727 --> 00:29:57.131
And you think your work
celebrates James Ulster?

591
00:29:57.831 --> 00:30:00.968
You know what I see
when I look at this. huh?

592
00:30:02.069 --> 00:30:03.571
It's a cheap knockoff.

593
00:30:03.705 --> 00:30:07.875
This work
is meant to be relished.

594
00:30:08.008 --> 00:30:10.944
All I see here

595
00:30:11.078 --> 00:30:15.750
is fear. hesitation.
a lack of discipline.

596
00:30:16.283 --> 00:30:18.352
-What is this?
-It's an assessment.

597
00:30:20.120 --> 00:30:22.022
It's a grade. really.

598
00:30:23.123 --> 00:30:24.325
Now. let's see.

599
00:30:26.093 --> 00:30:28.730
[softly] Oh. C-minus. Mmm.

600
00:30:29.631 --> 00:30:31.098
And that's being generous.

601
00:30:31.231 --> 00:30:33.367
It's soulless.

602
00:30:33.500 --> 00:30:34.536
[Jeb sniffs]

603
00:30:34.669 --> 00:30:35.804
Yeah.

604
00:30:36.904 --> 00:30:39.840
Did you even enjoy it? Huh?

605
00:30:40.709 --> 00:30:44.845
Did you get a rush?
An erection. even? [chuckles]

606
00:30:45.379 --> 00:30:48.783
No. no. no. no. no.
I don't think you did. No. no.

607
00:30:48.916 --> 00:30:51.985
I think you were scared.

608
00:30:52.119 --> 00:30:53.287
I was afraid I'd get caught.

609
00:30:53.954 --> 00:30:55.222
Oh. I could tell.

610
00:30:58.727 --> 00:31:02.363
When you're doing work
in my name.

611
00:31:03.364 --> 00:31:04.398
it has to be worthy.

612
00:31:06.668 --> 00:31:09.903
I speak through Will Trent now.

613
00:31:10.705 --> 00:31:12.607
He's the closest
thing I have to a son.

614
00:31:13.874 --> 00:31:16.210
-But she said--
-Oh. my daughter.

615
00:31:16.343 --> 00:31:17.444
She's nobody.

616
00:31:18.011 --> 00:31:20.582
[chuckles] You...

617
00:31:20.715 --> 00:31:23.551
You were scammed. [chuckles]

618
00:31:23.685 --> 00:31:26.086
I hope you didn't give her
your Social Security number.

619
00:31:26.220 --> 00:31:27.488
I don't understand.

620
00:31:27.622 --> 00:31:30.257
Well. that's as clear as
a bell. you unwashed simpleton.

621
00:31:33.661 --> 00:31:35.429
Sit up straight
when you talk to me.

622
00:31:37.231 --> 00:31:40.869
My name. my legacy. is being
polluted by this bitch.

623
00:31:41.001 --> 00:31:43.036
and you and I are
gonna stop her blasphemy.

624
00:31:44.071 --> 00:31:48.308
Or I could just sit here

625
00:31:49.209 --> 00:31:53.548
and remove your fingernails
one by one until you come
to your senses.

626
00:31:53.681 --> 00:31:57.652
[chuckles] No one...
No one will stop me.
I mean. they love me here.

627
00:31:57.786 --> 00:32:00.655
They can't get enough
of Will Trent.

628
00:32:02.222 --> 00:32:03.892
Are you starting to see...

629
00:32:05.827 --> 00:32:08.563
why I chose this guy
as my vessel?

630
00:32:12.166 --> 00:32:13.902
How can I help you. Mr. Ulster?

631
00:32:14.903 --> 00:32:16.270
[Will sighs]

632
00:32:16.403 --> 00:32:17.605
Tell me...

633
00:32:19.206 --> 00:32:21.576
what is Adelaide...

634
00:32:22.577 --> 00:32:23.645
doing?

635
00:32:26.246 --> 00:32:29.651
I don't know. [chuckles]
She don't talk to me. uh...

636
00:32:29.784 --> 00:32:30.951
No? Oh.

637
00:32:31.084 --> 00:32:33.320
I get my instructions
from somebody else.

638
00:32:35.657 --> 00:32:36.957
His name is The Commander.

639
00:32:37.926 --> 00:32:39.092
Ah.

640
00:32:39.226 --> 00:32:41.962
And how do I talk
to The Commander. huh?

641
00:32:42.630 --> 00:32:44.465
Um... [gulps]

642
00:32:45.600 --> 00:32:48.837
They'll only listen if they
hear it d-directly from me.

643
00:32:48.969 --> 00:32:49.970
Oh.

644
00:32:50.471 --> 00:32:51.840
Well. huh.

645
00:32:52.807 --> 00:32:54.308
arrange a meeting.

646
00:32:54.876 --> 00:32:55.910
Huh?

647
00:32:56.778 --> 00:32:58.979
Ah. [chuckles] Yeah.

648
00:33:00.515 --> 00:33:02.149
[gunfire]

649
00:33:06.420 --> 00:33:07.354
Damn.

650
00:33:07.488 --> 00:33:08.489
[Amanda chuckles]

651
00:33:08.623 --> 00:33:11.291
That is very hot.

652
00:33:11.992 --> 00:33:14.495
-Now your turn.
-Okay.

653
00:33:15.697 --> 00:33:17.364
-Okay. [chuckles]
-[Amanda chuckles]

654
00:33:18.499 --> 00:33:21.335
Now if you raise your gun.
you have to be ready to use it.

655
00:33:21.468 --> 00:33:23.370
-Always aim for center mass.
-Okay. [exhales]

656
00:33:23.505 --> 00:33:26.206
-Okay. Feet.
-Feet.

657
00:33:26.340 --> 00:33:28.208
-Shoulders.
-Shoulders.

658
00:33:28.776 --> 00:33:31.378
Okay. Breathe.

659
00:33:32.680 --> 00:33:35.917
visualize. and shoot.

660
00:33:38.318 --> 00:33:39.654
[Amanda laughs]

661
00:33:39.787 --> 00:33:42.524
-Oh. my God. [chuckles]
-Attagirl. You did it.
[chuckles]

662
00:33:42.657 --> 00:33:44.191
I'm gonna look into
getting one for myself.

663
00:33:44.324 --> 00:33:45.827
Well. let's do it now.

664
00:33:48.997 --> 00:33:51.933
Listen. Casey. I got
a bad feeling about Dallas.

665
00:33:52.065 --> 00:33:53.701
-You need protection.
-You're right.

666
00:33:53.835 --> 00:33:56.738
I just want to do
a little research first.
but I promise I will.

667
00:33:56.871 --> 00:33:57.839
Well. just take mine.

668
00:33:57.972 --> 00:33:59.339
I can't. You need it for work.

669
00:33:59.473 --> 00:34:01.308
No. No. no. no.
This is my personal gun.

670
00:34:01.976 --> 00:34:05.212
I mean... [chuckles]
...you've already shown that
you're comfortable with it.

671
00:34:05.345 --> 00:34:07.582
Listen. hang on to it
till you get your own.

672
00:34:07.715 --> 00:34:09.249
Put it somewhere safe.

673
00:34:12.219 --> 00:34:13.555
Thank you. Amanda.

674
00:34:14.187 --> 00:34:17.190
Oh. look. you're in my office.

675
00:34:17.324 --> 00:34:18.927
Yeah. low blood sugar.

676
00:34:19.059 --> 00:34:21.729
But. I have to say.
I like it in here.
It's quiet. great snacks.

677
00:34:21.863 --> 00:34:25.867
Yeah. okay.
don't get too comfortable.
Who's on the phone?

678
00:34:26.000 --> 00:34:29.369
I'm on hold
with the archive library
at Ronaldo's music school.

679
00:34:29.504 --> 00:34:33.206
Turns out that this
fast-food restaurant he visited
was only 20 miles from there.

680
00:34:33.340 --> 00:34:35.043
Traffic cameras
put him at the campus.

681
00:34:35.175 --> 00:34:37.110
-Nice.
-Oh. oh. hi. Yeah.

682
00:34:38.913 --> 00:34:40.748
Oh. wow. [scoffs]

683
00:34:41.716 --> 00:34:44.852
Ronaldo checked out a master's
thesis from 25 years ago.

684
00:34:45.753 --> 00:34:48.790
[♪ orchestra playing symphony]

685
00:35:09.276 --> 00:35:10.310
[phone buzzes]

686
00:35:12.914 --> 00:35:13.982
[buzzing continues]

687
00:35:14.114 --> 00:35:17.085
[mutters] Excuse me.

688
00:35:18.753 --> 00:35:19.954
I am at the symphony. What?

689
00:35:20.088 --> 00:35:22.122
Ronaldo stole
the composition from Claudia.

690
00:35:22.255 --> 00:35:23.558
What?

691
00:35:23.691 --> 00:35:25.125
<i>We're thinking after</i>
<i>she heard the first rehearsal.</i>

692
00:35:25.258 --> 00:35:27.028
she realized what he'd done.
confronted him.

693
00:35:27.160 --> 00:35:30.197
and when he didn't come clean.
she followed him to the motel
and killed him.

694
00:35:30.330 --> 00:35:32.132
Geez. her seat's
right next to mine.

695
00:35:32.265 --> 00:35:35.103
Good. Keep an eye on her.
We're on our way to the
symphony hall now with backup.

696
00:35:35.235 --> 00:35:36.269
You got it.

697
00:35:37.939 --> 00:35:39.841
[♪ symphony continues]

698
00:35:53.955 --> 00:35:55.123
Claudia!

699
00:36:04.799 --> 00:36:07.835
[♪ symphony continues.
suspenseful]

700
00:36:18.513 --> 00:36:21.115
Claudia. Come out.

701
00:36:23.483 --> 00:36:25.753
[Claudia] Shh.
They're playing right above us.

702
00:36:47.141 --> 00:36:50.678
Claudia. I see you.

703
00:36:54.515 --> 00:36:55.550
[door closes]

704
00:37:00.253 --> 00:37:02.623
[♪ continues. joyful]

705
00:37:16.804 --> 00:37:21.109
Claudia Sobinsky.
you're under arrest for the
murder of Ronaldo Benetti.

706
00:37:21.241 --> 00:37:24.045
Quiet. This is the best part.

707
00:37:32.854 --> 00:37:36.490
Twenty-five years ago.
I showed this piece to Ronaldo.

708
00:37:38.059 --> 00:37:40.460
and he convinced me
it wasn't any good.

709
00:37:42.230 --> 00:37:45.265
I was so young and insecure.

710
00:37:47.001 --> 00:37:48.536
I believed him.

711
00:37:52.073 --> 00:37:53.875
But I hear it now.

712
00:37:57.277 --> 00:37:59.147
I was good. [sobs]

713
00:38:04.417 --> 00:38:05.820
-Yes.
-[sniffles]

714
00:38:06.453 --> 00:38:07.487
You were.

715
00:38:15.630 --> 00:38:20.101
Please just let me listen
until the end.

716
00:38:22.302 --> 00:38:24.238
Then I promise
I'll go peacefully.

717
00:38:55.837 --> 00:38:56.971
[chuckling. crying]

718
00:38:59.774 --> 00:39:03.878
[♪ crescendoes]

719
00:39:04.812 --> 00:39:06.914
Come on through. We gotta go.

720
00:39:09.550 --> 00:39:11.919
-[♪ music stops]
-[cheering]

721
00:39:39.313 --> 00:39:40.447
Leon was right.

722
00:39:41.349 --> 00:39:42.283
I do want that.

723
00:39:42.415 --> 00:39:46.020
The husband.
the kid. all of it.

724
00:39:47.121 --> 00:39:49.290
Yeah. it's pretty great.

725
00:39:49.857 --> 00:39:50.892
[softly] Yeah.

726
00:39:52.226 --> 00:39:54.662
[siren wails in distance]

727
00:40:04.071 --> 00:40:06.107
[♪ mysterious music plays]

728
00:40:09.043 --> 00:40:10.111
I'm sorry. can I help you?

729
00:40:10.878 --> 00:40:12.313
Jeb says Ulster
speaks through you.

730
00:40:14.382 --> 00:40:15.415
Right.

731
00:40:16.183 --> 00:40:18.085
You are The Commander.

732
00:40:20.021 --> 00:40:21.689
Adelaide must really trust you.

733
00:40:21.822 --> 00:40:23.357
We understand each other.

734
00:40:24.491 --> 00:40:26.060
She helped me see
what real freedom is.

735
00:40:26.193 --> 00:40:27.228
Killing?

736
00:40:28.729 --> 00:40:29.797
Hurting innocent people?

737
00:40:29.931 --> 00:40:32.800
No one is innocent.

738
00:40:35.603 --> 00:40:38.739
I know what it's like
to be angry.

739
00:40:39.807 --> 00:40:43.144
There are days.
more than I'd like to admit.

740
00:40:44.745 --> 00:40:47.248
when I think my anger
might consume me.

741
00:40:49.216 --> 00:40:54.822
But killing doesn't make you
feel free or powerful.

742
00:40:54.956 --> 00:40:57.892
no matter who it is or why.

743
00:40:59.860 --> 00:41:01.796
It eats away at your soul.

744
00:41:06.100 --> 00:41:07.134
What's your name?

745
00:41:09.570 --> 00:41:10.705
Hey.

746
00:41:11.205 --> 00:41:14.442
If you know where
Antonio Morales is.
you need to tell me now.

747
00:41:14.575 --> 00:41:15.776
[The Commander scoffs]

748
00:41:15.910 --> 00:41:18.079
Don't let Adelaide get
you into any more trouble.

749
00:41:18.212 --> 00:41:20.648
Yeah. she said
you'd try to save me.

750
00:41:23.617 --> 00:41:25.485
-What's this?
-We'll be in touch.

751
00:41:27.088 --> 00:41:31.158
If you follow me.
I will tell her.

752
00:41:32.326 --> 00:41:33.761
And if that happens.

753
00:41:34.762 --> 00:41:36.697
I'm not sure what
she'll do to Antonio.

754
00:41:38.933 --> 00:41:39.967
Talk soon.

755
00:41:41.202 --> 00:41:42.570
[♪ tense music plays]

756
00:41:49.844 --> 00:41:52.847
[phone ringing]

757
00:41:54.181 --> 00:41:55.216
[phone beeps]

758
00:41:56.283 --> 00:41:59.120
-Casey.
<i>-Amanda. he's here!</i>

759
00:41:59.253 --> 00:42:01.489
-Who? Dallas?
<i>-He's in the house!</i>

760
00:42:01.622 --> 00:42:03.357
Go get the gun.
Remember what I taught you.

761
00:42:03.491 --> 00:42:05.493
[Dallas] <i>Come back here.</i>
<i>you bitch! I'm gonna kill you.</i>

762
00:42:05.626 --> 00:42:07.061
[pounding on door. loud crash]

763
00:42:07.194 --> 00:42:09.497
I-I'm sending the cops.
You know. ju-just hold tight.

764
00:42:09.630 --> 00:42:11.198
[Casey] <i>No. no!</i>

765
00:42:11.766 --> 00:42:12.933
[gunshot]

766
00:42:13.067 --> 00:42:14.035
Casey?

767
00:42:14.168 --> 00:42:15.936
[gunshots]

767
